# Architecture Rules

## Patterns
- **Server Components** by default; use `"use client"` only when needed (forms, interactivity)
- **API Routes** in `src/app/api/` for all backend logic
- **Validation** with `zod` schemas in `src/lib/validators/`
- **Types** in `src/lib/types.ts`
- **No ORMs** — this is a demo app; use in-memory data store

## File Organization
```
src/
  app/
    page.tsx              # Landing page
    register/page.tsx     # Registration form
    onboarding/page.tsx   # Profile completion
    dashboard/page.tsx    # Welcome dashboard
    api/
      register/route.ts   # POST /api/register
      validate-email/route.ts # POST /api/validate-email
  components/
    OnboardingForm.tsx
    EmailInput.tsx
    PasswordInput.tsx
    ProfileForm.tsx
  lib/
    validators/
      email.ts
      password.ts
      profile.ts
    types.ts
    store.ts              # In-memory data store
```

## Error Handling
- API routes: try/catch with consistent error responses
- Client: error boundaries for unexpected errors
- Forms: field-level validation with zod
